[00:07.60]Make Me a Faithful Tree
[00:11.16]Verse 1
[00:14.72]You planted me in mercy’s soil,
[00:18.28]Beside the living stream;
[00:21.84]Your hidden roots sustain my soul
[00:25.40]With grace I cannot see.
[00:28.96]Refrain
[00:32.52]O make me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[00:36.08]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[00:39.64]That all the fruit my life shall bear
[00:43.20]Brings glory unto Thee.
[00:46.77]Verse 2
[00:50.33]What grows upon my waiting limbs
[00:53.89]Reveals what feeds my heart;
[00:57.45]For bitter roots bear bitter fruit,
[01:01.01]And pride will tear apart.
[01:04.57]Refrain
[01:08.13]O make me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[01:11.69]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[01:15.25]That all the fruit my life shall bear
[01:18.81]Brings glory unto Thee.
[01:22.37]Verse 3
[01:25.94]A good tree cannot evil yield,
[01:29.50]Nor rotten fruit be sound;
[01:33.06]The life within determines what
[01:36.62]Upon its bough is found.
[01:40.18]Bridge
[01:43.74]Search me, Lord, and try my ways,
[01:47.30]Expose what lies beneath;
[01:50.86]Replace the stone within my chest
[01:54.42]With roots of living faith.
[01:57.98]Let living water flood my soul,
[02:01.54]Let every dry place bloom;
[02:05.10]Till branches heavy with Your grace
[02:08.67]Break forth in holy fruit.
[02:12.23]Final Refrain
[02:15.79]O keep me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[02:19.35]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[02:22.91]Till every fruit from every branch
[02:26.47]Brings praise eternally.
[02:30.03]Outro
[02:33.59]I’m rooted in You,
[02:37.15]Rooted in You.
[02:40.71]Every branch, every leaf,
[02:44.27]All for You.
[02:47.83]Prune me, shape me,
[02:51.40]Grow Your truth.
[02:54.96]I’m rooted in You,
[02:58.52]Only You.
